hec.h5

Class Dataset

  • java.lang.Object
    • hec.h5.Dataset

  • public class Dataset
extends java.lang.Object
    HDF5 interface library: Datasets This library provides wrapper methods for HDF5 storage and retrieval of HDF5 data for the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers Hydrologic Engineering Center (HEC) and Engineer Research and Development Center Environmental Laboratory (ERDC-EL).
    Since:
    August 2017

      • read_2D_array_float

        public static float[][] read_2D_array_float(int datasetID,
                                            long startrow,
                                            long startcol,
                                            long nrows_hdf,
                                            long ncols_hdf)
                                     throws Globals.H5InterfaceException
        Read 2D array (float)

        This method can read an entire dataset or a subset, including row and column vectors.

        Example Settings:

        • Entire dataset, 100 rows x 50 columns:
          startrow = 0, startcol = 0, nrows_hdf = 100, ncols_hdf = 50
        • Subset of dataset at starting at (row, col) = (5,7), 30 rows x 20 columns:
          startrow = 5, startcol = 7, nrows_hdf = 30, ncols_hdf = 20
        • Row vector at index 5, 100 values (e.g. write all cross-section data for a time step):
          startrow = 5, startcol = 0, nrows_hdf = 1, ncols_hdf = 100
        • Column vector at index 5, 100 values (e.g., write time series for a cross-section):
          startrow = 0, startcol = 5, nrows_hdf = 100, ncols_hdf = 1
        Parameters:
        datasetID - Dataset identifier
        startrow - Index of first row of subset
        startcol - Index of first column of subset
        nrows_hdf - Number of rows in subset
        ncols_hdf - Number of columns in subset
        Returns:
        2D data array (float[][])
        Throws:
        Globals.H5InterfaceException - HDF5 dataset exception

      • create_2D_dataset

        public static int create_2D_dataset(int locID,
                                    java.lang.String datasetName,
                                    long nrows_hdf,
                                    long ncols_hdf,
                                    int datatypeID,
                                    boolean chunk_in_time,
                                    int kind_nbytes,
                                    boolean isCompressed)
                             throws Globals.H5InterfaceException
        Create a 2D HDF5 dataset: numerical type

        Note: compression and chunking are optional

        Parameters:
        locID - File or group identifier, where dataset will be created
        datasetName - Name of dataset to create
        nrows_hdf - Number of rows in HDF5 dataset (C convention: [row, column])
        ncols_hdf - Number of columns in HDF5 dataset (C convention: [row, column])
        datatypeID - Data type identifier for dataset
        chunk_in_time - If true, chunk in the time dimension, i.e., chunks will consist of one or more HDF5 dataset rows. If false, chunk in the space dimension.
        kind_nbytes - Number of bytes of floating point or integer data types
        isCompressed - If true, chunk and compress the dataset and set one dimension to unlimited. If chunk_in_time is also true, the current and maximum row dimensions will be set to create a dataset with only one row and an unlimited number of rows. If chunk_time is false, the current and maximum column dimensions will be set to create a dataset with only one column and an unlimited number of columns.
        Returns:
        Dataset identifier (integer)
        Throws:
        Globals.H5InterfaceException - HDF5 dataset exception

                             throws Globals.H5InterfaceException
        Create a 1D HDF5 dataset: numerical type

        Note: compression and chunking are optional

        Parameters:

        datasetName - Name of dataset to create
        nvals - Number of values in HDF5 dataset
        datatypeID - Data type identifier for dataset
        kind_nbytes - Number of bytes of floating point or integer data types
        isCompressed - If true, chunk and compress the dataset. Set the current dataset dimensions to one value and the maximum dimensions to unlimited.
        Returns:
        Dataset identifier (integer)

      • write_2D_array

        public static void write_2D_array(int datasetID,
                                  long startrow,
                                  long startcol,
                                  long nrows_data,
                                  long ncols_data,
                                  float[][] data)
                           throws Globals.H5InterfaceException
        Write 2D array (float)

        This method can write an entire dataset or a subset, including row and column vectors.

        Example Settings:

        • Entire dataset, 100 rows x 50 columns:
          startrow = 0, startcol = 0, nrows_hdf = 100, ncols_hdf = 50
        • Subset of dataset at starting at (row, col) = (5,7), 30 rows x 20 columns:
          startrow = 5, startcol = 7, nrows_hdf = 30, ncols_hdf = 20
        • Row vector at index 5, 100 values (e.g. write all cross-section data for a time step):
          startrow = 5, startcol = 0, nrows_hdf = 1, ncols_hdf = 100
        • Column vector at index 5, 100 values (e.g., write time series for a cross-section):
          startrow = 0, startcol = 5, nrows_hdf = 100, ncols_hdf = 1
        Parameters:
        datasetID - Dataset identifier
        startrow - Index of first row of subset
        startcol - Index of first column of subset
        nrows_data - Number of rows in data array
        ncols_data - Number of columns in data array
        data - 2D data array to write
        Throws:
        Globals.H5InterfaceException - HDF5 dataset exception
